\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {5.2}{\ignorespaces The above boxplot shows the answers of the subjects for the optimal number of frequencies. For coarse foam 9.4 and for granite tile 10.2 were the mean optimum value, where 10 was chosen by the half of the subjects in coarse foam experiment. For steel wool, oak and fine foam the mean optimum values by 14, 11.8 and 10.7 were chosen respectively. All 50 choices, 10 subjects per each 5 material, result in the mean number of 11.22 on average and the maximum number of frequencies is 20, which can be interpreted as the optimal number is between 12 and 20 according to this study.}}{26}
