\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {6.1}{\ignorespaces The haptic showroom which contains the experiment materials can be seen above. The materials from left to right: granite tile, steel wool, coarse foam, oak, fine foam. Simulation starts at the center directly across the objects where interactions can easily be performed by the users. At the beginning, original signals are activated for all materials. Users can switch to LPC synthesized signals, to inverse discrete Fourier transformed signals and to signals generated via major frequencies in the simulation. The user speed is detected during interaction and the corresponding sound is displayed according to the speed interval. Users control the gray ball in the picture with the haptic device to explore and interact with objects.}}{30}
